error.signature: SNS delivery to endpoint failed: Endpoint is disabled or does not exist

verdict.summary: SNS message delivery to a subscription endpoint failed due to disabled endpoint, permission issues, or endpoint errors.

dead_ends.action: Republish the same message repeatedly to a disabled endpoint
dead_ends.why_fails: Disabled endpoints reject all messages; republishing without re-enabling won't help

dead_ends.action: Delete and recreate the SNS topic to fix delivery issues
dead_ends.why_fails: Recreating the topic loses all subscriptions and requires reconfiguring all subscribers

workarounds.action: Enable delivery status logging to identify the specific failure reason
workarounds.how: Configure delivery status logging in SNS topic attributes, then check CloudWatch Logs for delivery failure details

workarounds.action: Re-enable disabled endpoints or resubscribe for platforms like SQS, Lambda, HTTP
workarounds.how: aws sns set-subscription-attributes or delete/recreate the subscription for the failing endpoint

preceded_by.condition: SNS topic policy denies the publishing principal
